==English==
===Noun===
'''diminuendo''' (''plural'' '''diminuendos''')

===Etymology===
Italian ''diminuendo'', present participle of ''[[diminuire]]'', to diminish, to decrease

#(''music'') An instruction to play gradually more softly, denoted by a long, narrow angle with its [[apex]] on the right. Abbreviation: dimin.

====Antonym====
*[[crescendo]]

